<br>
My main concern is that so many posts on this topic and similar ones revolve around duplicating something good that another rogue class already has.  I am very much against cookie cutter classes.  Making us all exactly the same would indeed make us balanced... but it would be boring to play.<br>
<br>
Regarding Celtic Dual, it isn't that great for us but it is decent, as pointed out above.  When it comes to helping Blade Masters, I feel it would be better to give them double parry for dual wielding since most of them that I know pull agro easily (filborg dual wield) and almost all CD styles cause a penalty to defense.  If they could parry with both blades (at least mathematically) it would make them a very good class to play in the way a NS with high evade/dodge makes a pretty good tank.<br>
<br>
It seems that there are several SBs that are going for the jugular on the Infiltrators and it is just wrong.  Since they never did this before the LA nerf, I am guessing they are using Infs as whipping boys because they are mad about LA.  That is not cool.  I have never played an infiltrator but I know I kill them as often as they kill me so they aren't uber.  I certainly never feared them the way I used to fear SBs.  <br>
<br>
IMO, the main love that needs to be extended to SBs is the opportunity to respec.  However, I think that most of them would not change their LA spec because in spite of the DF nerf, LA is still a great line.  I respect the fact that the SBs are pissed and I think they have a right to be pissed, but there is no need to start marching for cookie cutter classes and please don't start preying on Infs because it is just not true.  No offense to Infs, but no one says, &quot;Oh God, please don't let an Inf find me out here alone.&quot;  Infs aren't scaring &quot;uber.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/2/02 2:44:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3410.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: caution</span><hr size=1> Double parry for duel wielders would go far to balance the classes--it wouldn't affect the assasins, and it would help the classes that needed it most.  It makes sense--two weapons should mean a better chance of parrying someone's blow.  Zerkers probably have lower parry skill than the other hybrids, too so this is an advantage to them (or even if they gave it to the only to other realms, it'd still make their 50 LA style more useful).   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utiwgy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiwgy </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/2/02 3:37:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3410.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=