<br>
BUT this is detracting from the view that maybe SB’s have been nerfed too hard.  I disagree wholeheartedly that they should be brought back to their former glory but maybe they need some love too.<br>
<br>
I still do not believe that a slash infil is better than an SB.  So far all we have seen is one persons logs against one single Infil who is apparently the best buffed, best equipped Inf on the server.  The first log shows them about equal and the second shows totally different results.  This is not proof of anything and how can it be when we have two totally different results?  This alone shows the data to be non representative.  <br>
<br>
In the same thread Mill says that SB’s now fight doing 50% less damage than they used to.  Yet still he claims they were never overpowered.  No offense to Mill here since at least he is trying to provide us with logs and suchlike, I just think the data is getting taken out of context.  How can they have been anywhere near equal before if the SB used to do 50% more damage than now?<br>
<br>
I think the fact is that IMHO SB’s used to be overpowered.  Now Infils and SB’s are equal in melee. However, I do agree that they should not be equal since an infil gets more options.  Let’s try and even this out. <br>
<br>
SB’s Have 2-H weapon which is undoubtedly a bonus, they also get extra hits.  Inf’s get more spec points’ which is a bonus and get to choose thrust or slash.  NS’s get the shout spell which is a bonus (or would be if it ‘worked).<br>
<br>
These things should be worked on to increase the effectiveness of the classes.  We should not go down the road of the cookie cutters.  I would say increase the damage for SB’s (not as high as it used to be though) and/or give them the different weapon spec option, NS’s are easy to fix.  Up that shout damage.  I think that this last option will be done.  It’s just a matter of time.<br>
<br>
If we can all agree and not ask for unreasonable things then let’s all work together and try and get Mythic to listen.  Of course they won’t listen right now because whatever you say, someone else will disagree with.  Why should they listen?<br>
<br>
NS’s do not have this problem and I believe that this is THE reason they will get the damage upped on their shout spell.  Why should they not do it, it won’t piss anyone off and will make some people happy?  If they make the same amount of people happy that they piss off they gain nothing.  The only way to get Mythics attention is to present a united front.  The only way to present a untied front is to be honest with each other and ourselves.  If you want to look for balance then be honest with your limitations and your abilities.  Don’t cry wolf or exaggerate because it will only destroy the case you are trying to make.<br>
<br>
Baiul.<br>
